body:
@wyli I wasn't able to reproduce the issue:

```
docker run --rm python:3.7 bash -c "pip install mlflow protobuf==3.15.6 && python -c 'import mlflow; mlflow.set_tracking_uri(\"test\")'"
```

works fine. Are you sure you're using `protobuf 3.15.6`?

Sorry I forgot to mention that the flag `export PROTOCOL_BUFFERS_PYTHON_IMPLEMENTATION=python` is used when launching the tests. I'll look into a minimal example to reproduce this.

the version in the report is correct ~please see one such error log if interested: https://github.com/Project-MONAI/MONAI/runs/6636024010?check_suite_focus=true~

```
docker run --rm -e PROTOCOL_BUFFERS_PYTHON_IMPLEMENTATION=python python:3.7 bash -c "pip install mlflow protobuf==3.15.6 && python -c 'from mlflow.tracking.client import MlflowClient'"
```

can reproduce the issue.
https://github.com/mlflow/mlflow/pull/5970 indicates `protobuf>= 3.19.4` works with `PROTOCOL_BUFFERS_PYTHON_IMPLEMENTATION=python`. Can you upgrade `protobuf` used in your repo?
Or you can pin `protobuf<4.0.0` and remove `PROTOCOL_BUFFERS_PYTHON_IMPLEMENTATION` if `monai` depends on other ML packages that are incompatible with `protobuf>4.0.0`.

Thanks @harupy for the suggestions. monai doesn't directly use protobuf, it uses mlflow and mlflow requires protobuf. Ideally we don't pin down protobuf version from monai's perspective... Using  mlflow v1.26.0 everything was fine, and if the issue reported here is expected as of version 1.26.1 (or won't be fixed), from monai's perspective we'll think about some workaround...
Is there a reason you're using protobuf 3.15.6?

No specific reason, it happens to be in a specific version of a pytorch docker image that we wanted to support. And the flag was introduced in the ci testing because of other recent compatibility issues in pytorch/tensorboard with protobuf 4.21.
Btw why do you use `PROTOCOL_BUFFERS_PYTHON_IMPLEMENTATION=python` in `protobuf==3.15.6`? It's required when using `protobuf>4.0.0` with proto code generated in `<3.19.0`.

https://github.com/Project-MONAI/MONAI/blob/61a0dc35b8a5edf78487b30c02c7aa0e51fc3409/runtests.sh#L18

I think you can skip this line in `protobuf < 4.0.0`.

@harupy just wanted to confirm the issue reported here is a bug since 1.26.1 and won't be fixed in the near future in. Mlflow? (For monai related fixes I think it'll be great to discuss them in monai's repo.)

> won't be fixed in the near future in. Mlflow?

We probably won't. I think this is a bug in `protobuf`. Proto code generated in `protoc 3.19.4` doesn't work in `protobuf < 3.19.4` when `PROTOCOL_BUFFERS_PYTHON_IMPLEMENTATION=python` is defined.

MLflow 1.26.1 works in `protobuf > 3.12.0` without `PROTOCOL_BUFFERS_PYTHON_IMPLEMENTATION=python`.
MLflow 1.26.1 works in `protobuf >= 3.19.4` with `PROTOCOL_BUFFERS_PYTHON_IMPLEMENTATION=python` (may also work with `3.19.3`, `3.19.2`, and `3.19.1` but haven't tested them yet).

> > won't be fixed in the near future in. Mlflow?
> 
> 
> 
> We probably won't. I think this is a bug in `protobuf`. Proto code generated in `protoc 3.19.4` doesn't work in `protobuf < 3.19.4` when `PROTOCOL_BUFFERS_PYTHON_IMPLEMENTATION=python` is defined.

Thanks for confirming.
